<section class="place">

<h2>Siddheshwar Temple</h2>

<p>
Siddheshwar Temple is one of the most important spiritual landmarks in Solapur.
Dedicated to Lord Siddheshwar, a form of Lord Shiva, the temple is located near the
peaceful Siddheshwar Lake in the center of the city. Thousands of devotees visit the
temple every day and it becomes very crowded during the Siddheshwar Yatra festival.
</p>

<div class="gallery">
<img src="images/siddeshwar.jpg" alt="Siddheshwar Temple">
<img src="images/siddeshwar_night.jpg" alt="Siddheshwar Temple Night View">
</div>

</section>


<section class="place">

<h2>Pandharpur</h2>

<p>
Pandharpur is one of the most sacred pilgrimage towns in Maharashtra and is located
about 70 km from Solapur. It is famous for the Vitthal Rukmini Temple dedicated to
Lord Vitthal. During the Ashadhi and Kartiki Ekadashi festivals, millions of devotees
participate in the Wari pilgrimage and visit this holy town.
</p>

<div class="gallery">
<img src="images/pandharpur1.jpg" alt="Pandharpur Temple">
<img src="images/pandharpur2.jpg" alt="Pandharpur Wari">
</div>

</section>


<section class="place">

<h2>Tuljapur</h2>

<p>
Tuljapur is a famous pilgrimage destination located near Solapur. It is known for the
Tulja Bhavani Temple dedicated to Goddess Bhavani. Devotees from many parts of
Maharashtra visit this temple to seek blessings.
</p>

<div class="gallery">
<img src="images/tuljapur1.jpg" alt="Tuljapur Temple">
<img src="images/tuljapur2.jpg" alt="Tuljapur Temple View">
<img src="images/tuljapur3.jpg" alt="Tuljapur Temple Entrance">
</div>

</section>


<section class="place">

<h2>Solapur Fort</h2>

<p>
Solapur Fort, also known as Bhuikot Fort, is a historic monument located in the city.
The fort was built during the Bahmani Sultanate period and later ruled by several
dynasties. The architecture reflects the military design of medieval India and
represents the rich historical heritage of Solapur.
</p>

</section>

